description:
Can we trust God's promises? Is God fickle, or will He keep the promises He makes to us? 
Many politicians and world leaders today are notoriously fickle, making promises that they change, or never even fulfill. Is God like that? Or is He really trustworthy?

What is the correlation between prophecy in the Bible and God's consistency? Is God as credible as the Bible makes Him to be? How do we know for certain that God will do everything He says He will do? 

Discover how the problems within Babylon demonstrate the role of prophecy in the Bible. This lecture demonstrates that you can trust God's promises in light of Daniel 7. Learn the significance of prophecy in the Bible and discover evidence that God is trustworthy.
